com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.helper

Class HashPool<E>

  • Object
    • AbstractMap<K,V>
      • HashMap<Integer,ArrayList<E>>
        • com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.helper.HashPool<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of object to use.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Integer,ArrayList<E>>

    public class HashPool<E>
extends HashMap<Integer,ArrayList<E>>
    This class is a special data structure used for Xilinx FPGA devices to help reduce memory footprint of objects. It keeps exactly one copy of an object of type E and maintains a unique integer enumeration of each object. It depends on the type E's equals() and hashCode() function to determine uniqueness.
